159 /** This test aims to provoke the assertion that checks if the battery system fits the internal configuration */
160 void testMXM_ConstructBalancingBufferTest(void) {
161  /* skip this test if the BMS configuration does not fit to this test
162  (we cannot run with more cells than Maxim supports) */
163  if ((BS_NR_OF_CELL_BLOCKS_PER_MODULE > MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_CELLS_PER_MODULE)) {
164  TEST_PASS_MESSAGE("This test is skipped due to the configuration of the BMS.");
165  }
166  TEST_ASSERT_FAIL_ASSERT(MXM_ConstructBalancingBuffer(NULL_PTR));
167  DATA_BLOCK_BALANCING_CONTROL_s balancingTable = {.header.uniqueId = DATA_BLOCK_ID_BALANCING_CONTROL};
168  MXM_BALANCING_STATE_s balancingInstance = {.pBalancingControl_table = &balancingTable};
169  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_ConstructBalancingBuffer(&balancingInstance));
170 }

204  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_5X_STATE_UNSENT, mxm_instance.requestStatus5x);
205  MXM_5XSetStateRequest_ExpectAndReturn(

207  MXM_STATEMACH_5X_WRITEALL,
208  mxm_instance.batteryCmdBuffer,

210  STD_OK);
211  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_HandleStateWriteall(&mxm_instance, 42u));
212 }

243 void testMXM_HandleStateReadallUnsent(void) {
244  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_5X_STATE_UNSENT, mxm_instance.requestStatus5x);
245  const uint8_t registerAddress = 21u;
246  /* recreate a local variant of the expected command buffer */
247  MXM_5X_COMMAND_PAYLOAD_s commandBuffer = {
248  .regAddress = registerAddress,
249  .lsb = 0,
250  .msb = 0,
251  .model = modelForTest,
252  };
253  MXM_5XSetStateRequest_ExpectAndReturn(
254  mxm_instance.pInstance5X, MXM_STATEMACH_5X_READALL, commandBuffer, &mxm_instance.requestStatus5x, STD_OK);
255  bool functionReturnValue;
256  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(functionReturnValue = MXM_HandleStateReadall(&mxm_instance, registerAddress, 42u));
257  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(false, functionReturnValue);
258 }

276 void testMXM_HandleStateReadallProcessed(void) {
277  mxm_instance.requestStatus5x = MXM_5X_STATE_PROCESSED;
278  MXM_5XGetRXBuffer_ExpectAndReturn(mxm_instance.pInstance5X, mxm_instance.rxBuffer, MXM_RX_BUFFER_LENGTH, STD_OK);
279  MXM_5XGetLastDCByte_ExpectAndReturn(mxm_instance.pInstance5X, 84u);
280  bool functionReturnValue;
281  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(functionReturnValue = MXM_HandleStateReadall(&mxm_instance, 21u, 42u));
282  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(true, functionReturnValue);
283  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(MXM_5X_STATE_UNSENT, mxm_instance.requestStatus5x);
284  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(42u, mxm_instance.operationSubstate);
285  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(84u, mxm_instance.dcByte);
286 }

292 void testMXM_ProcessOpenWire1SatelliteAlternatingPattern(void) {
293  /* with only one module, the entry of the LSB should be in the third
294  position of the RX buffer and the MSB in the fourth */
295  mxm_instance.rxBuffer[2] = 85; /* 0b01010101 */
296  mxm_instance.rxBuffer[3] = 170; /* 0b10101010 */
297  /* simulate 1 satellite */
298  MXM_5XGetNumberOfSatellites_ExpectAndReturn(mxm_instance.pInstance5X, 1);
299  /* don't care about the database call */
300  DATA_Write1DataBlock_IgnoreAndReturn(STD_OK);
301  TEST_ASSERT_PASS_ASSERT(MXM_ProcessOpenWire(&mxm_instance));
302 
303  /* check for the injected pattern */
304  for (uint8_t i = 0u; i < 8; i = i + 2) {
305  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(1, mxm_instance.pOpenWire_table->openWire[0][i]);
306  }
307  for (uint8_t i = 1u; i < 8; i = i + 2) {
308  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0, mxm_instance.pOpenWire_table->openWire[0][i]);
309  }
310  for (uint8_t i = 8u; i < MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_CELLS_PER_MODULE; i = i + 2) {
311  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(0, mxm_instance.pOpenWire_table->openWire[0][i]);
312  }
313  for (uint8_t i = 9u; i < MXM_MAXIMUM_NR_OF_CELLS_PER_MODULE; i = i + 2) {
314  TEST_ASSERT_EQUAL(1, mxm_instance.pOpenWire_table->openWire[0][i]);
315  }
316 }
